"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The function sns.set_style() is incorrectly used with the rc parameter. The rc parameter is not valid for set_style(), which only accepts style names as strings or a dictionary of parameters that are part of the style definition. The correct usage would be to call sns.set_style() with a style name like 'whitegrid' or 'darkgrid'.\", \"patch\": \"14c14\\n< sns.set_style(rc=style_dict)\\n---\\n> sns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n\"}"